article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 71, Monmouth, N.J. 54
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Scooby Johnson scored a game-high 22 points to help lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 71-54 win over Monmouth on Monday night. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (2-0) led for the entire contest, building its biggest margin with a 26-point lead with 7 minutes to play. Johnson, who shot 80 percent, also led the Islanders with five rebounds. Cedric Smith came off the bench to add 19 points while Josh Washington scored 13 points from the bench. Dejan Delic led the Hawks (1-4) with 20 points. Jhamar Youngblood came off the bench to add 16. Monmouth improved in the second half, playing the Islanders to a draw in that period after falling behind 40-23 at the break. The Islanders shot 58 percent from the field to 47 percent for Monmouth. It was the first meeting between the Texas and New Jersey schools.
